of corporate units (Corporate Units), at a stated amount of $50 per Corporate Unit, for a total stated amount of $1.725 billion. Net
proceeds from the issuance were approximately $1.682 billion. Each Corporate Unit is comprised of (i) a 1/40 undivided beneficial
ownership interest in $1,000 principal amount of Southern Company's Series 2019A Remarketable Junior Subordinated Notes due
2024, (ii) a 1/40 undivided beneficial ownership interest in $1,000 principal amount of Southern Company's Series 2019B
Remarketable Junior Subordinated Notes due 2027, and (iii) a stock purchase contract, which obligates the holder to purchase from
Southern Company, no later than August 1, 2022, a certain number of shares of Southern Company's common stock for $50 in cash.
