The valuation of certain commodity contracts requires the use of certain unobservable inputs. All forward pricing used in the
valuation of such contracts is directly based on third-party market data, such as broker quotes and exchange settlements, when that
data is available. If third-party market data is not available, then industry standard methodologies are used to develop inputs that
maximize the use of relevant observable inputs and minimize the use of unobservable inputs. Observable inputs, including some
forward prices used for determining fair value, reflect the best available market information. Unobservable inputs are updated using
industry standard techniques such as extrapolation, combining observable forward inputs supplemented by historical market and
other relevant data. Level 3 physical natural gas forward contracts include unobservable forward price
