Construction Projects
During 2019, Southern Power completed construction of and placed in service the 385-MW Plant Mankato expansion and the
Wildhorse Mountain facility, acquired and continued construction of the Skookumchuck facility, and continued construction of the
Reading facility. Total aggregate construction costs, excluding acquisition costs, are expected to be between $490 million and $535
million for the two facilities under construction. At December 31, 2019, total costs of construction incurred for the two facilities
under construction were $417 million and are included in CWIP. The ultimate outcome of these matters cannot be determined at
this time.
